{"version":2,"kind":"Article","sha256":"1a7778ff84d00d9083f5625e8e301308f7f70a8d2b659804cc2a4bdb55c1997c","slug":"papers","location":"/papers.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Process for Authoring Jupyter Related Academic Papers","content_includes_title":false,"license":{"content":{"id":"CC0-1.0","url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/zero/1.0/","name":"Creative Commons Zero v1.0 Universal","free":true,"CC":true}},"github":"https://github.com/jupyter/governance","copyright":"","numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"source_url":"https://github.com/jupyter/governance/blob/main/docs/papers.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/jupyter/governance/edit/main/docs/papers.md","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"papers.md","url":"/governance/build/papers-6740c1a022f9c98dad04362f865b344f.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This document describes the processes used to author Jupyter related academic\npapers, which are typically submitted to peer-reviewed journals. This does not\ninclude talks and posters submitted to conferences unless the conference also\npublishes written proceedings.","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"hAcw7LqGkb"}],"key":"jWZQHIFRUL"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"On one hand, the primary focus of Project Jupyter is on producing open-source\nsoftware. We are very much focused on writing code that delights our users. On\nthe other hand, Jupyter (and IPython) emerged out of an acadmic setting, where\nresearch and peer-reviwed publications are a primary focus. To this day, many\nof our core contributors have academic positions and active research programs.\nThis emphasis is also reflected in the usage of Jupyter across all areas of\nscientific research. Thus, in spite of a focus on writing software for users,\nJupyter remains a tool that is by and for researchers.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"qTjxy88zZs"}],"key":"DEIcOtvaeB"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Given this focus on research, the ongoing academic careers of many Jupyter\ncontributors, and our desire to have an impact on computing research, it is\nimportant for us to author and publish peer-reviewed papers on Jupyter itself.\nAuthoring these papers in the context of a large, open-source community\npresents a number of differences compared to many research collaborations.","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"fwfDL0fa0q"}],"key":"h0GbaGied9"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Principles","position":{"start":{"line":23,"column":1},"end":{"line":23,"column":1}},"key":"kHBc1h7vyP"}],"identifier":"principles","label":"Principles","html_id":"principles","implicit":true,"key":"YwX2tinLzU"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We have tried to create a process for authoring papers with the following\ngeneral principles in mind:","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"gYIRLvaPYQ"}],"key":"F6dGR5VCk0"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Inclusivity and generosity in authorship.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"WlghTCM8Wz"}],"key":"xODAyQhFE3"},{"type":"text","value":" Hundreds of individuals have\ncontributed to the different Jupyter subprojects. These contributions span\ncode, design, documentation, discussions, giving talks/tutorials, etc. We\nwant to be generous in extending authorship privileges and responsibilities\nto as many of these contributors as possible.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"tf55AlYHcQ"}],"key":"tbbRL5wdP4"}],"key":"BAsQZEvm7S"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Clear, explicit criteria for authorship.","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"kWyxfIBK5F"}],"key":"kxAXYlnvin"},{"type":"text","value":" While being generous, we want\nhave concrete, specific and auditable criteria for including individuals as\nauthors.","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"G7Lhh1wAOm"}],"key":"hqyyfktLbt"}],"key":"PJrcEAyKOL"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Openness.","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"key":"TNSO546zBn"}],"key":"csVkJllL5i"},{"type":"text","value":" The process of authoring papers should be open in the same way\nas the rest of the project’s work. Thus, all of our papers are written in the\npublic on GitHub.","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"key":"SiURcRs8T0"}],"key":"pGuzffsDQZ"}],"key":"boNkHozO19"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Accountability.","position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"key":"x3HnufgKuh"}],"key":"jjoYELsEHy"},{"type":"text","value":" Being an author on a paper is a privilege, but also\ninvolves responsibilities. The concrete processes described below elucidate\nthese responsibilities.","position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"key":"TKFxL8Nokr"}],"key":"Xaiu3GV3FE"}],"key":"sUwAHyaS4w"}],"key":"HSZTegCGvO"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":43,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We expect to author and submit papers to different types of journals. Different\njournals will have slightly different concrete processes that appropriately\nembody these principles.","position":{"start":{"line":43,"column":1},"end":{"line":43,"column":1}},"key":"YyovHULtOS"}],"key":"vLBDEXQSEz"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Author ordering","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1},"end":{"line":47,"column":1}},"key":"JFsvgHndrv"}],"identifier":"author-ordering","label":"Author ordering","html_id":"author-ordering","implicit":true,"key":"mV0T7R5Bqj"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":49,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In some academic fields, author ordering is used to implicitly communicate the level and significance of the individual’s contributions. We strongly feel this\nis misleading and misguided. Because of this, all Jupyter papers will use the\nfollowing author ordering policy:","position":{"start":{"line":49,"column":1},"end":{"line":49,"column":1}},"key":"F3Os2TbCqi"}],"key":"LS4QnOvAaS"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The first author will be listed as “Project Jupyter”;","position":{"start":{"line":53,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"key":"JcvCA948l2"}],"key":"JQogDaoRjp"}],"key":"k16fzYM9Oi"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Individual authors will follow in alphabetical order; and","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"key":"Q6HLYsx6gp"}],"key":"VfQAtgRL2j"}],"key":"g5R6bK2AGe"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"An explicit statement about the ordering will be included in the paper.","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"key":"Dc4cUCotVS"}],"key":"uo8q8VHSOW"}],"key":"hXUKi75aAF"}],"key":"RV7qw7aEfs"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":57,"column":1},"end":{"line":61,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Listing the first author as “Project Jupyter” is important as it means that in\nabbreviated citations, the author list will be “Project Jupyter, et al.” rather\nthan artificially showing the first alphabetical author’s name. This is common\npractice in academic field such as high energy physics where there are large\nnumbers of authors on papers.","position":{"start":{"line":57,"column":1},"end":{"line":57,"column":1}},"key":"lxxJRrGPp6"}],"key":"arLFRAZSm7"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Process for Journal of Open Source Software (JOSS)","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"key":"qfDqXpBGYq"}],"identifier":"process-for-journal-of-open-source-software-joss","label":"Process for Journal of Open Source Software (JOSS)","html_id":"process-for-journal-of-open-source-software-joss","implicit":true,"key":"YZKDyO68tz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The ","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"key":"ziPHF9RbtQ"},{"type":"link","url":"http://joss.theoj.org/","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Journal of Open Source Software","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"key":"eBWMykfoqe"}],"urlSource":"http://joss.theoj.org/","key":"FfYD39GrsA"},{"type":"text","value":" (JOSS) is a\npeer-reviewed, developer-friendly journal for research related software. JOSS\nis unique in that:","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"key":"a67mtqwcf5"}],"key":"qjYKKZbJ0p"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Each paper is associated with a single GitHub repository;","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"pjE42IxCza"}],"key":"dAlpXPJXha"}],"key":"IV7dvVtMF2"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The primary research artifact in the software itself; and","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"key":"eVR97VIw3i"}],"key":"DWUwIZNqHY"}],"key":"yDv3wfaapg"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":71,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The paper itself is a relatively brief markdown file in the software’s GitHub\nrepository, deferring details of the software to its own documentation.","position":{"start":{"line":71,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"key":"S44TBN9NFy"}],"key":"DK4BwUyemB"}],"key":"HarrnXnVKb"}],"key":"qd1vHZ6fc1"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":74,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It is our intention to publish a JOSS paper for each of our main, user-focused\nsubprojects (Notebook, JupyterLab, JupyterHub, nbconvert, ipywidgets, etc.).\nAll such paper should use the process described herein.","position":{"start":{"line":74,"column":1},"end":{"line":74,"column":1}},"key":"lalNRrvSpi"}],"key":"jRHNK8WaiU"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":78,"column":1},"end":{"line":78,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"JOSS authorship criteria","position":{"start":{"line":78,"column":1},"end":{"line":78,"column":1}},"key":"rJT8dIbIgL"}],"identifier":"joss-authorship-criteria","label":"JOSS authorship criteria","html_id":"joss-authorship-criteria","implicit":true,"key":"YjdMyUEf5b"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":80,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Our authorship criteria for JOSS papers are derived from those of the\n","position":{"start":{"line":80,"column":1},"end":{"line":80,"column":1}},"key":"Ou7YPdwBT0"},{"type":"link","url":"http://www.icmje.org/recommendations/browse/roles-and-responsibilities/defining-the-role-of-authors-and-contributors.html#two","position":{"start":{"line":80,"column":1},"end":{"line":80,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ICMJE","position":{"start":{"line":80,"column":1},"end":{"line":80,"column":1}},"key":"jAubD04tu9"}],"urlSource":"http://www.icmje.org/recommendations/browse/roles-and-responsibilities/defining-the-role-of-authors-and-contributors.html#two","key":"jbN7CRlwWx"},{"type":"text","value":":","position":{"start":{"line":80,"column":1},"end":{"line":80,"column":1}},"key":"b4zape15xn"}],"key":"VUznue4ndF"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Substantial contributions to the conception, design, or implementation of\nsoftware; this includes coding, visual design, documentation, testing,\ndiscussions and other such contributions; AND","position":{"start":{"line":83,"column":1},"end":{"line":83,"column":1}},"key":"QQ44aXtk2Q"}],"key":"rCasLRiVRG"}],"key":"C0UEO0a42A"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":86,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Final approval of the version to be published; AND","position":{"start":{"line":86,"column":1},"end":{"line":86,"column":1}},"key":"e6Chg8p0rV"}],"key":"ZY2wpXEkQA"}],"key":"pqQWq8Qhw3"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":87,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Agreement to be accountable for all aspects of the work in ensuring that\nquestions related to the accuracy or integrity of any part of the work are\nappropriately investigated and resolved.","position":{"start":{"line":87,"column":1},"end":{"line":87,"column":1}},"key":"ZAvrMNAswQ"}],"key":"K67IdEOWLV"}],"key":"mFh8JXFjlY"}],"key":"lJ4RzQHRlW"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Anyone who satisfies and is willing to accept these responsibilities and commitments is welcome to be an author on any of our JOSS publications.","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"mjoH8aF4Jo"}],"key":"qfDx6cO0MU"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"JOSS process","position":{"start":{"line":93,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"key":"KsMF0i8biU"}],"identifier":"joss-process","label":"JOSS process","html_id":"joss-process","implicit":true,"key":"A9DcGr6ghW"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":95,"column":1},"end":{"line":95,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The following process should be used to author any Jupyter related JOSS paper:","position":{"start":{"line":95,"column":1},"end":{"line":95,"column":1}},"key":"Hs17mAmvFa"}],"key":"pAGSQlsQL5"},{"type":"heading","depth":4,"position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1. Someone agrees to be the Coordinator for a paper","position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"key":"fMq6zwWYW0"}],"identifier":"id-1-someone-agrees-to-be-the-coordinator-for-a-paper","label":"1. Someone agrees to be the Coordinator for a paper","html_id":"id-1-someone-agrees-to-be-the-coordinator-for-a-paper","implicit":true,"key":"p0NNJnGp1i"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":101,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A single JOSS paper will be associated with a single Jupyter repository. The\nCoordinator will usually be a senior project contributor, Steering Council\nmember, or leader of that subproject.","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"key":"pwOx3vSivv"}],"key":"BCfpoacWUv"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1},"end":{"line":105,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The role of the Coordinator is to implement this process for that paper. They\ndo not have to write the JOSS paper themselves, but they will work with the\ncommunity to organize the writing of the paper.","position":{"start":{"line":103,"column":1},"end":{"line":103,"column":1}},"key":"NTclMgwJYW"}],"key":"KC4z1pw6w3"},{"type":"heading","depth":4,"position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"2. Open an issue and announce the writing of the paper","position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"key":"pitucI2WMS"}],"identifier":"id-2-open-an-issue-and-announce-the-writing-of-the-paper","label":"2. Open an issue and announce the writing of the paper","html_id":"id-2-open-an-issue-and-announce-the-writing-of-the-paper","implicit":true,"key":"UAoFTQML0e"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":111,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Coordinator should open an issue to organize the writing of the paper on\nthat repository and then announce to the Jupyter Google Group that the paper is\nbeing worked on and that anyone can contribute (with a link to the issue).","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"jjBHzKJF7q"}],"key":"BJwmedZIbp"},{"type":"heading","depth":4,"position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"3. Draft the paper in the repository","position":{"start":{"line":113,"column":1},"end":{"line":113,"column":1}},"key":"iPD7CCHApk"}],"identifier":"id-3-draft-the-paper-in-the-repository","label":"3. Draft the paper in the repository","html_id":"id-3-draft-the-paper-in-the-repository","implicit":true,"key":"vgXdxXYjIN"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At this point, the Coordinator should organize the writing of the actual paper.","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"uSx3UCKlqN"}],"key":"MxPCJSa0WX"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"J6Afi0u17P"},{"type":"link","url":"http://joss.theoj.org/about","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"JOSS Author Guidelines","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"oD8mWQgxjI"}],"urlSource":"http://joss.theoj.org/about","key":"qfHMnAf8GD"},{"type":"text","value":" detail the format and\nrequirements of a JOSS paper. In general this will involve creating a ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"Ozoj5Neldo"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"paper","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"B1fZyIatfr"},{"type":"text","value":"\nsubdirectory in the root of the repository with two files: ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"W3X5TBEHrr"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"paper.md","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"NgQL6AKVKB"},{"type":"text","value":" and\n","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"uywfmN66Y2"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"paper.bib","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"xLint3uoOY"},{"type":"text","value":". The paper should be written using our standard processes for pull\nrequests and code review.","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"fmqZYbpB1a"}],"key":"ThX0ex3sgA"},{"type":"heading","depth":4,"position":{"start":{"line":123,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"3. Email potential authors","position":{"start":{"line":123,"column":1},"end":{"line":123,"column":1}},"key":"Ze8fGPCn5F"}],"identifier":"id-3-email-potential-authors","label":"3. Email potential authors","html_id":"id-3-email-potential-authors","implicit":true,"key":"ZHCL8Sw3zl"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":127,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once a final draft of the paper has been merged into the repository, the\nCoordinator should email all potential authors of the paper, inviting them to\nparticipate. Usually this will include at least two emails:","position":{"start":{"line":125,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"key":"NRVvUQOYm4"}],"key":"sM6zZjqifu"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1},"end":{"line":134,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1},"end":{"line":131,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Individually email all contributors listed in the Git log of the repository.\nThis list can be generated using the Git command ","position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1},"end":{"line":129,"column":1}},"key":"SiLdiCnrGC"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"git log --all --format='%cN <%cE>' | sort -u","position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1},"end":{"line":129,"column":1}},"key":"fCV5JliVDM"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1},"end":{"line":129,"column":1}},"key":"bqHsUwLqIE"}],"key":"EyGzqv1nfC"}],"key":"ySKKDzd9dh"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":132,"column":1},"end":{"line":134,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Email the main Jupyter Google Group to include folks not listed in the Git\nlog.","position":{"start":{"line":132,"column":1},"end":{"line":132,"column":1}},"key":"rfjT8RK5yd"}],"key":"FsJ6R8KWf5"}],"key":"eHmepx0A7m"}],"key":"HLApx2gAsx"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":138,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In addition, the Coordinator should send personal emails to individuals, such\nas students, who are new to writing academic publications, explaining why we\nare writing a paper, and encouraging them to participate. These personal emails\nshould cc the individual’s mentor or advisor if applicable.","position":{"start":{"line":135,"column":1},"end":{"line":135,"column":1}},"key":"oNJ7jnj0sR"}],"key":"rCmrUT7onN"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":140,"column":1},"end":{"line":140,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Both of these emails should include:","position":{"start":{"line":140,"column":1},"end":{"line":140,"column":1}},"key":"fc8WudoPzG"}],"key":"zNObzKcqDH"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":142,"column":1},"end":{"line":147,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":142,"column":1},"end":{"line":142,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"A verbatim copy of the above JOSS authorship criteria;","position":{"start":{"line":142,"column":1},"end":{"line":142,"column":1}},"key":"IjJaoz6Gv4"}],"key":"Aph2bj52P6"}],"key":"y7oU9tHaBZ"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":143,"column":1},"end":{"line":144,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"A description the tasks each individual needs complete to be an author on the\npaper;","position":{"start":{"line":143,"column":1},"end":{"line":143,"column":1}},"key":"PZJGU8ipJg"}],"key":"irYUv2fBT5"}],"key":"dGpdmnIxjN"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":145,"column":1},"end":{"line":145,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","child